  "prompt": "Are Kodak cameras still around?",
  "response": "Yes, Kodak cameras are still around, but the company's role in the photography market has evolved over the years. Eastman Kodak Company, commonly known as Kodak, was once a dominant player in the film and camera industry. With the advent of digital photography, Kodak faced significant challenges and eventually shifted its focus.\n\nKodak has moved away from manufacturing traditional consumer cameras and film. Instead, it has concentrated on digital imaging solutions, commercial printing, and other technology services. However, Kodak's brand still exists, and you'll find Kodak-branded digital cameras, instant print cameras, and other imaging products, often produced in collaboration with other manufacturers under licensing agreements.\n\nAdditionally, Kodak continues to serve professional markets with high-end imaging products and services. Though it's not the giant it once was, Kodak remains relevant in the imaging and technology sectors.",
